exif:ImageDescription: With a bouquet of roses in her hand, First Lady Jacqueline Kennedy (1929 - 1994) and, behind her, U.S. President John F. Kennedy (1917 - 1963), greet the public at Love Field airport during a campaign tour in Dallas, Texas, on November 22, 1963. The President was assassinated later that day. (Photo by Art Rickerby/Time & Life Pictures/Getty Images)
